106
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:37,760
So blockchains themselves are often marketed as word computers.

107
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:42,640
But if you look at all the blockchains that are available today, they simply cannot run

108
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:49,360
faster than a single server, and it is extremely expensive to process transactions on blockchain.

109
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:51,360
Well, you may say, OK, wait, wait, wait.

110
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:56,020
This cannot be the case because we have been building blockchain scalability technology

111
00:08:56,020 --> 00:09:01,960
for years, so we should be able to build anything on blockchain today, right?

112
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:04,600
Well, unfortunately, that is not the case.

113
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:08,160
Let me give you a very concrete example here.

114
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:15,840
So if you have ever used any centralized exchanges in the past, you all have used this kind of

115
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:19,800
feature where if you trade it loud in this month, in the next month, you get a trading

