00:14:14,150 --> 00:14:18,950
So I mentioned like we have a lot of adoptions but what is actually Brevis?

174
00:14:18,950 --> 00:14:20,950
What is actually inside this magic box?

175
00:14:20,950 --> 00:14:28,190
Well, the centerpiece of our entire computing stack is something called a Pico ZKVM.

176
00:14:28,190 --> 00:14:29,910
So what is a ZKVM?

177
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:36,670
Well, ZKVM is a general purpose virtual machine that you can run any program on top of it.

178
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:42,470
And it's ZK and the ZK enabled means that you can actually run any program and generate

179
00:14:42,470 --> 00:14:47,670
a verifiable proof of the program's computing result.

180
00:14:47,670 --> 00:14:53,670
Now ZK or like kind of a cryptographic proof is actually very hard to learn mathematical

181
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:54,670
concept.

182
00:14:55,150 --> 00:15:01,110
Before you have something like Pico ZKVM, all you can do is actually write the program

183
00:15:01,110 --> 00:15:05,150
in mathematical equations if you want to kind of make it a provable.

184
00:15:05,150 --> 00:15:10,870
But with ZKVM, what you can do is you can just write very high level language just like

185
00:15:10,870 --> 00:15:18,030
you write any software and then you can make this entire program provable and verifiable.

186
00:15:18,030 --> 00:15:24,610
So this is also how we're changing how blockchains are built and operated today.

187
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:31,290
So Ethereum itself is actually moving towards a ZK oriented architecture.

188
00:15:31,290 --> 00:15:36,770
So instead of every validator in Ethereum, like millions of them, repeat the same kind

189
00:15:36,770 --> 00:15:39,470
of computation again and again.

190
00:15:39,470 --> 00:15:44,890
What now you can do is to have one validator do a very large amount of computation and

191
00:15:44,890 --> 00:15:50,210
generate a very small proof that you can use so that everyone else can just verify the

192
00:15:50,210 --> 00:15:55,450
proof of the computation is done correctly and then the blockchain can move forward.

193
00:15:55,450 --> 00:16:00,610
What this means is that you can actually use any hardware you have today, like even on

194
00:16:00,610 --> 00:16:06,730
your phone, to run a full node of Ethereum and reach maximal decentralization and at

195
00:16:06,730 --> 00:16:08,930
the same time maximal scalability.

196
00:16:08,930 --> 00:16:15,270
Like I'm talking about a hundred times better scalability of today's Ethereum blockchain.

197
00:16:15,330 --> 00:16:21,690
So to do this, what you need is an extremely fast ZK VM so that you can actually catch

198
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:24,670
up with the blockchain production time.

199
00:16:24,670 --> 00:16:29,830
Like for Ethereum blocks it is produced every 12 seconds, so you need to actually be able

200
00:16:29,830 --> 00:16:34,030
to generate the proof of block execution within that 12 seconds.

201
00:16:34,030 --> 00:16:40,710
And this is what we do, ZK VM is as fast as ZK VM that allows you to generate the ZK proof

202
00:16:40,710 --> 00:16:47,350
for a blockchain execution within 12 seconds for 99% of Ethereum blocks.

